<div class="page-header"><h1>Why this matters</h1>
<p>Pflugerville ISD is the largest school district in ACC's service area that has not joined the taxing district. With approximately 25,300 students, PfISD is nearly twice the size of Georgetown ISD, the next-largest non-district ISD. Every surrounding community has joined. We have not.</p></div>

<div class="prose">
<h2>The cost gap</h2>
<p>ACC charges two rates. In-district residents (those who pay the ACC property tax) pay $85 per credit hour in tuition and fees. Out-of-district residents pay $286 per credit hour. The difference is $201 per credit hour, driven entirely by the out-of-district fee.</p>
<p>For a full-time student taking 30 credit hours per year, that gap is $6,030 annually. Over a two-year associate degree, it is $12,060. For a student in ACC's free tuition pilot program, the gap is even more stark: an in-district student pays $0 in tuition and fees, while a PfISD student still pays $201 per credit hour, or $3,015 per semester at 15 credits. Source: <a href="https://admissions.austincc.edu/tuition-costs/" target="_blank">ACC Admissions</a>, <a href="https://catalog.austincc.edu/college-entry/paying-for-college/acc-free-tuition-pilot-program/" target="_blank">ACC Free Tuition Pilot</a>.</p>

<div class="callout">
<strong>The math:</strong> Round Rock, Leander, Manor, Del Valle, Hays, Elgin, and Lockhart residents all pay $85/credit hour. Pflugerville residents pay $286. Same programs, same instructors, same campuses. Different price.
</div>

<h2>What happened in 2018</h2>
<p>Pflugerville ISD held an ACC annexation vote on November 6, 2018. The measure failed 53.45% to 46.55%. The petition drive collected 3,556 voter signatures, exceeding the 5% threshold of 2,710. Opposition was concentrated outside Pflugerville city limits among homeowners concerned about the projected median property tax increase of $268.63 per year.</p>
<p>Source: <a href="https://communityimpact.com/austin/round-rock-pflugerville-hutto/vote/2018/11/06/early-voting-returns-show-pfisd-voters-rejecting-acc-annexation/" target="_blank">Community Impact, Nov 2018</a>.</p>

<h2>What changed since 2018</h2>
<p>ACC launched a free tuition pilot in 2024 that now serves nearly 10,000 students. PfISD students who qualify still pay the $201/credit hour out-of-district fee. That penalty did not exist in 2018 because the free tuition program did not exist.</p>
<p>Lockhart ISD voted to join the ACC district in November 2024, passing 61.2% to 38.8%. Within one year, ACC enrollment from Lockhart surged from under 200 to over 600 students, with 214 first-time ACC students. ACC opened a physical center in downtown Lockhart with specialized trade labs. Source: <a href="https://sites.austincc.edu/newsroom/2025/11/03/one-year-later-acc-enrollment-surges-in-lockhart-following-annexation-vote/" target="_blank">ACC Newsroom, Nov 2025</a>.</p>
<p>ACC has now maintained 12 consecutive years of no in-district tuition or general fee increases. Workforce and healthcare program enrollment grew at double-digit rates in 2025-26. Texas HB 8 (2023) shifted state community college funding toward performance and workforce outcomes, increasing state investment in credential programs. PfISD is building a new CTE center opening in 2027, and the Downtown East development (late 2026/early 2027) creates additional infrastructure for workforce training.</p>

<h2>What other communities experienced</h2>
